d the industry as a local identifier and indicates how the industry’s efforts have rekindled the residents’ interest in agriculture as a significant element of regional heritage and local identities. Revealing how the profiles of local narratives and commemorations become entwined with social, cultural, economic, and political power, Meaningful Pasts illuminates the fact that local narratives retain their relevance only if residents find them meaningful in their day-to-day lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCollective memoryzOntariozNiagara (Regional municipality). 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geography.2bisacsh  aBest sociology books.  aCanada geography.  aCanadian History.  aCanadian heritage.  aNiagara wine.  aNiagara.  acollective memory.  ahistory books.  amass media.  amnemonics.1 aRipmeester, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079737440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148752874440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487528744423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487528744/original  a978-3-11-079737-4  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles